column5: Call Pizza Hut the minute you get into the line to cross the border, then pick it up on the way to your destination.
Does anyone have suggestions for supper in International Falls?
I've eaten at the Chocolate Moose (no relation to the restaurant in Ely, MN) and found it to be reasonably priced, though the food was a little plain.
Go to the the Border Bar Pizza restaurant. It has great food, and the scenery is tough to beat!
the wife and i love the chocolate moose. i'm kindof partial to the chicken fried steak. lots of food for the buck, good tasting too.
Another vote for the Chocolate Moose
I like the Chocolate Moose for breakfast and the Border Bar for dinner. The "Stickman" at the BB is FANTASTIC!
Ditto on the stickman at border bar!!!!!!!!!
We had an excellent dinner at "The Spot" last year
